The paper deals with the mathematical structure and algorithmic aspects of reconciling gene trees with species trees, which is a problem in computational biology. The paper uses graph theory and combinatorial optimization techniques to derive a complete characterization of time-consistent reconciliations. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
